approve(address,uint256).details: See {IERC20-approve}. NOTE: If `value` is the maximum `uint256`, the allowance is not updated on `transferFrom`. This is semantically equivalent to an infinite approval. Requirements: - `spender` cannot be the zero address.

borrowUsdc(uint256).details: Borrows specified amount of USDC from USDC vault

params.usdcAmount: Amount of USDC to borrow (0 = borrow max safe amount)

borrowWeth(uint256).details: Step 2 of delta-neutral strategy: Borrow WETH using USDC as collateral

decimals().details: Decimals are computed by adding the decimal offset on top of the underlying asset's decimals. This "original" value is cached during construction of the vault contract. If this read operation fails (e.g., the asset has not been created yet), a default of 18 is used to represent the underlying asset's decimals. See {IERC20Metadata-decimals}.

getUserNonceInfo(address).details: Returns used nonces and remaining capacity (255 max usable, 256th is final)

lendUsdc().details: Step 1 of delta-neutral strategy: Provide USDC as collateral

lendWeth().details: Deposits available WETH into WETH vault as collateral

name().details: Returns the name of the token.

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

previewWithdrawalSubAccount(address).details: Useful for advanced users who want to prepare transactions

rebalance(uint256,uint256,uint256,uint25.details: Complete strategy transition that handles pool management and position rebalancing

params.newInitialState: New initial state for pool reinstallation
params.targetUsdcBorrow: Amount of USDC to borrow against collateral (0 = don't borrow any)
params.targetWethBorrow: Amount of WETH to borrow against collateral (0 = don't borrow any)
params.usdcToLend: Amount of USDC to lend as collateral (0 = don't lend any)
params.wethToLend: Amount of WETH to lend as collateral (0 = don't lend any)

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby disabling any functionality that is only available to the owner.

repayUsdc(uint256).details: Repays USDC debt using available USDC balance

params.usdcAmount: Amount of USDC to repay (0 = repay all debt)

repayWeth(uint256).details: Step 3 of delta-neutral strategy: Repay borrowed WETH

params.wethAmount: Amount of WETH to repay (0 = repay all debt)

symbol().details: Returns the symbol of the token, usually a shorter version of the name.

transfer(address,uint256).details: See {IERC20-transfer}. Requirements: - `to` cannot be the zero address. - the caller must have a balance of at least `value`.

transferFrom(address,address,uint256).details: See {IERC20-transferFrom}. Skips emitting an {Approval} event indicating an allowance update. This is not required by the ERC. See {xref-ERC20-_approve-address-address-uint256-bool-}[_approve]. NOTE: Does not update the allowance if the current allowance is the maximum `uint256`. Requirements: - `from` and `to` cannot be the zero address. - `from` must have a balance of at least `value`. - the caller must have allowance for ``from``'s tokens of at least `value`.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

withdrawToSubAccount(uint256,address,add.details: Creates sub-account automatically and transfers proportional position

getUserNonceInfo(address).notice: Get user's current nonce usage for sub-accounts

installPool((address,address,address,uin.notice: Install new EulerSwap pool with specified parameters

lendUsdc().notice: Lend all available USDC to the USDC vault

lendWeth().notice: Lend WETH as collateral to WETH vault

previewProportionalWithdraw(address).notice: Calculate proportional withdrawal amounts for a user

previewWithdrawalSubAccount(address).notice: Preview what sub-account address will be used for next withdrawal

rebalance(uint256,uint256,uint256,uint25.notice: Execute full rebalance: uninstall pool, rebalance positions, reinstall with new parameters

repayWeth(uint256).notice: Repay WETH debt using available WETH balance

totalAssets().notice: Total assets are just USDC balance in this simple implementation

withdrawToSubAccount(uint256,address,add.notice: Withdraw with automatic sub-account creation for user isolation
